-- SQL AND --
/* SQL AND is a logical operator in SQL that allows you to select only rows that satisfy two conditions. */

-- SQL NOT --
/* SQL NOT is a logical operator that you can put before any conditional statement to select rows for which that statement is false / exclude rows for which the statement is true. */

